### Detailed Government Tender Announcement for Psychological Testing Services

**Title:** Correctional Service Canada - Psychological Testing

**Reference Number:** cb-316-9819908
**Amendment Number:** 7

**Solicitation Number:** 21120-24-4477931
**Publication Date:** 28-Nov-2023
**Tender Closing Date:** 08-Jan-2024 14:00:00

**Notice Type:** Request for Proposal
**Procurement Method:** Competitive - Open Bidding

**Objective:**
Correctional Service Canada (CSC) requires a service provider to conduct psychological testing services for the recruitment of Correctional Officers and Primary Workers across various locations in Canada.

**Scope of Work:**
A minimum of one (1) Senior Clinical Psychologist and one (1) Clinical Psychologist must be provided to administer psychological testing and clinical interviews. The Contractor must evaluate the psychological readiness of candidates in CSC's recruitment processes for Correctional Officers and Primary Workers.

**Contract Duration:**
The contract will be for a period of two (2) years, with the option to renew for three (3) additional one-year periods.

**Evaluation Criteria:**
The winning bidder will be selected based on the lowest priced compliant bid.

**Important Details:**
* Security Requirements apply to this contract.
* Documents may be submitted in either English or French.
* The Crown reserves the right to negotiate with suppliers on any procurement.
* Bidders may request a debriefing on the results of the bid solicitation process within 15 working days of receipt of the results.

**Contact Information:**
* Diana Todorova
* Phone: (343) 552-1625
* Email: diana.todorova@csc-scc.gc.ca

**Tender Documents:**
All tender documents and evaluation criteria can be downloaded from the Canada Buys/Tender Opportunities website.

**Additional Information:**
Procurement Assistance Canada (PAC) offers seminars to businesses interested in learning how to sell goods and services to the Government of Canada. These seminars are free and cover a range of topics, including the federal government contracting process, searching for opportunities on the Buy and Sell/Tenders website, bidding on opportunities, and registering in supplier databases. The full schedule of seminars can be found on the BuyandSell.gc.ca website.
